---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '~/components/Nav.astro';
import FathomTag from '~/components/FathomTag.astro';
---

<Base
  title="writ — cryptographic audit trail for AI calls"
  description="Open-source Go SDK that wraps anthropic.Client and writes a Merkle-linked audit chain of every AI call. EU AI Act Article 12 compliance posture."
>
  <FathomTag slot="head" />

  <Nav />
  <main id="main">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 pt-20 pb-16 border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-6">
        <div
          class="inline-block font-mono text-xs text-accent border border-accent/30 rounded px-2 py-1 bg-accent/5"
        >
          pre-launch · early access
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-ink">writ</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-muted leading-relaxed max-w-narrow">
          Cryptographic audit trail for AI calls. Drop-in Go SDK that wraps
          <code class="font-mono text-base text-ink bg-surface-raised px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
            >anthropic.Client</code
          >
          and writes a tamper-evident Merkle chain of every LLM call your system makes.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 pt-2">
          <a
            href="mailto:hello@opskernel.io?subject=writ early access"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-brand-gradient text-surface font-medium px-5 py-3 rounded-md hover:opacity-90 active:opacity-80 transition-opacity"
          >
            Request early access
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/opskernel-io/writ"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center border border-ink-subtle/30 text-ink font-medium px-5 py-3 rounded-md hover:border-ink-subtle/60 transition-colors"
          >
            GitHub →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Problem -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          EU AI Act Article 12 requires that AI system operators log AI decisions in a way auditors
          can independently verify. Most teams have no audit trail at all. The ones that do log to a
          database — mutable rows that can be modified after the fact, which don't satisfy an
          independent verification requirement.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-8">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">How it works</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-accent text-sm">01 — drop-in SDK</div>
            <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
              <code class="font-mono text-xs text-ink bg-surface-raised px-1 py-0.5 rounded"
                >writ.New(cfg)</code
              >
              wraps your existing
              <code class="font-mono text-xs text-ink bg-surface-raised px-1 py-0.5 rounded"
                >*anthropic.Client</code
              >. Zero behaviour change to your application logic.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-accent text-sm">02 — Merkle chain</div>
            <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Every call is hashed to the previous entry, producing a tamper-evident chain. Any
              post-hoc modification to any entry breaks chain integrity — detectably.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-accent text-sm">03 — policy gate</div>
            <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Optional Rego rules run before each call. Violations are logged and blocked before the
              LLM executes — you don't pay for calls your policies should have rejected.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick start -->
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-display font-medium text-lg text-ink">Quick start</h3>
          <pre
            class="bg-surface-raised border border-ink-subtle/20 rounded-lg p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm font-mono text-ink leading-relaxed"><code>go get github.com/opskernel-io/writ

cfg := writ.Config&#123;ChainPath: "/var/log/myapp/audit.jsonl"&#125;
client, _ := writ.New(cfg, anthropic.NewClient())

// Drop-in — call identical to sdk usage
msg, _ := client.Messages.New(ctx, anthropic.MessageNewParams&#123;...&#125;)

// Verify chain integrity at any time
result, _ := writ.VerifyStream(cfg.ChainPath, nil)
fmt.Println("entries:", result.Count, "ok:", result.Valid)</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Compliance posture -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-6">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">
          EU AI Act Article 12 posture
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          writ v0 addresses three Article 12 §1 requirements directly. eIDAS-qualified timestamping
          and retention management are deferred to a commercial tier; the chain entry schema
          reserves the slot.
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-ink-subtle/20">
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-ink-muted">Requirement</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-medium text-ink-muted">Status</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-subtle/10">
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-ink">Log AI system inputs and outputs</td>
                <td class="py-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-ok font-mono text-xs">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> MET
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-ink-muted text-xs ml-2">every call written to audit chain</span>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-ink">Tamper-evidence</td>
                <td class="py-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-ok font-mono text-xs">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> MET
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-ink-muted text-xs ml-2"
                    >Merkle chain; modification breaks integrity detectably</span
                  >
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-ink">Independent verification path</td>
                <td class="py-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-ok font-mono text-xs">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> MET
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-ink-muted text-xs ml-2">
                    <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface-raised px-1 py-0.5 rounded"
                      >writ verify</code
                    > CLI reads chain without SDK dependency
                  </span>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-ink">eIDAS-qualified timestamp</td>
                <td class="py-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-warn font-mono text-xs">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">⏳</span> Commercial tier
                  </span>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-ink">6-month minimum retention</td>
                <td class="py-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-warn font-mono text-xs">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">⏳</span> BYO
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-ink-muted text-xs ml-2"
                    >v0 is pre-commercial; chain is append-only JSONL</span
                  >
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What's in v0 -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-6">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">What's in v0</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          {
            [
              'Go SDK (writ.New() wrapper)',
              'Merkle audit chain (SHA-256 linked entries)',
              'OPA codification gate (optional, hot-reload without redeploy)',
              'Corrupt-chain recovery (segment boundary + recovery flag)',
              'Access protection (AllowedCallers, ChainProtected mode)',
              'CLI verifier (writ verify)',
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-ink-muted">
                <span class="text-ok mt-0.5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
                  ✓
                </span>
                {item}
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1 pt-2">
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-subtle font-mono">Not in v0:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">
            RFC 3161 / qualified timestamp authority (commercial tier), retention management,
            dashboard.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Known limitations -->
    <section class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section border-b border-ink-subtle/10">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">
          Known limitations
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-muted">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-warn mt-0.5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
            <span>
              <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Process-level boundary only.</strong> Transitive dependencies
              that call the Anthropic API directly bypass the writ wrapper. See the threat model ADR.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-warn mt-0.5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
            <span>
              <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Single-process append assumption.</strong> No concurrent
              writers. Parallel processes writing to the same chain file produce undefined chain integrity.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-warn mt-0.5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
            <span>
              <strong class="text-ink font-medium">No timestamp authority.</strong> Chain entries are
              hashed but not RFC 3161 timestamped. eIDAS-qualified timestamps are a commercial-tier feature.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Early access CTA -->
    <section id="access" class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section">
      <div class="max-w-narrow mx-auto text-center space-y-5">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl tracking-tight text-ink">Early access</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          writ is pre-launch. The GitHub repo is private; access is granted on request. If you're
          building on the Anthropic SDK and need an auditable trail for EU AI Act compliance, reach
          out.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center pt-2">
          <a
            href="mailto:hello@opskernel.io?subject=writ early access"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-brand-gradient text-surface font-medium px-5 py-3 rounded-md hover:opacity-90 active:opacity-80 transition-opacity"
          >
            Request early access
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/opskernel-io/writ"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center border border-ink-subtle/30 text-ink font-medium px-5 py-3 rounded-md hover:border-ink-subtle/60 transition-colors"
          >
            GitHub (private — request access)
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-ink-subtle pt-2">
          Apache 2.0. OSS tier is free; commercial tier (timestamps + managed retention) is
          post-launch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
